main event: One object with flashing lights observed over Plum Tree Island, Virginia on January 24, 1965.
interesting points: The object was approximately 75 feet across and 10-15 feet thick,It had flashing lights and lifted off at a 45-degree angle,The object remained fixed for about 5 minutes before departing to the north at high speed,The observer used 20-power binoculars for the sighting,The sighting duration was 1.5 hours and no physical evidence was reported.
witness description: Service Engineer, Electronic Instrumentation, 34 years old, from Hampton, Virginia
